race.description: In Memory Of Garry Fraser Handicap (Bm58)
race.comment: LADY ZODIAC (2) has transferred to the Martino stable and returns from a 163-day spell. Opened last prep with a close third in a BM64 at Gosford which is excellent form for a race of this calibre. No trial form to assist since making the move but expect she is forward enough to run very well. BOLD DESIGN (4) led and gave a kick but was nailed close to home when resuming over 1000m at this track a fortnight ago. Lightly raced four-year-old who will improve off that run - just needs luck from the wide alley to be right in the thick of things. PELETTE (7) has contested better races than this all prep with mixed results. At her best over this distance and she has a liking for Muswellbrook. Can turn things around. STIORRA (13) doesn't win out of turn but recent efforts have been solid. One for the exotics. SAPPHIRE KISS (10) did little first-up at Newcastle but will find this easier.
